<subSubSection id="F6CF6578FFAD6328FF3100D3BC5134FF" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="BE6A36F3FFAD6328FF3100D3BC5134FF" blockId="4.[160,1156,1213,1274]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="8CA1EAE1FFAD6328FF3100D3B96F34D2" bold="true" box="[160,291,1213,1239]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name refers to the strongly wrinkled depression half a whorl preceding the peristome, from the Latin 
<taxonomicName id="79D54D70FFAD6328FE62008FBA1F34FF" authorityName="Silva &amp; Mendes-Júnior &amp; Simone" authorityYear="2022" box="[499,595,1249,1274]" class="Gastropoda" family="Solaropsidae" genus="Solaropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="caperata">
<emphasis id="8CA1EAE1FFAD6328FE62008FBA1F34FF" box="[499,595,1249,1274]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">caperata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(a feminine adjective), meaning wrinkle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6CF6578FFAD6328FF310149BA5B3583" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BE6A36F3FFAD6328FF310149BA5B3583" blockId="4.[160,1155,1319,1414]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="8CA1EAE1FFAD6328FF310149B9513544" bold="true" box="[160,285,1319,1345]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Shell large, with strong wrinkled depression half a whorl preceding the peristome, causing folds inferiorly. Spire dome-shaped, suture shallow. Peristome ample. Umbilicus widely opened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6CF6578FFAD632AFF3101DABA2A3182" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="85" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" type="description">
<paragraph id="BE6A36F3FFAD632AFF3101DAB9F130E8" blockId="4.[160,1156,1460,1728]" lastBlockId="6.[160,1156,142,237]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="85" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="8CA1EAE1FFAD6328FF3101DAB96135CB" bold="true" box="[160,301,1460,1486]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Description.</emphasis>
Shell globose-discoid, ~ 
<quantity id="792D9B16FFAD6328FDDF01DBBAEF35CB" box="[590,675,1461,1486]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="50.0">50 mm</quantity>
in maximum diameter, ~5¼ whorls; outline rounded; suture shallow, practically plane (
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAD6328FD2F01B9BB0E35F5" box="[702,834,1495,1520]" captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="5.[160,235,1259,1282]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetId="figure-112@5.[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 2–7. Holotype of Solaropsis caperata MZSP 144000 (W = 50.2 mm): 2, apical view; 3, inferior view; 4, left view; 5, apertural view; 6, detail of region half a whorl preceding the peristome, showing characteristic depression, dorsal-slightly inferior view; 7, detail of apical region, apical view, scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457015/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Figures 4–5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAD6328FCC101B9BBA735F5" box="[848,1003,1495,1520]" captionStart="Figures 10–16" captionStartId="7.[160,235,840,863]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetId="figure-3@7.[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 10–16. Paratypes of Solaropsis caperata. 10, MZSP 154136 (W 45.1 mm), frontal view; 11, same apical view; 12, same, inferior view; 13, MZSP 154137 (W 39.0 mm), frontal view; 14, same, frontalslightly inferior view to show depression; 15, same, apical view; 16, inferior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457021/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">10 and 13–14</figureCitation>
). Protoconch of 
<quantity id="792D9B16FFAD6328FF520194B9403616" box="[195,268,1530,1555]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
, with about two whorls, smooth, uniform beige (
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAD6328FCCF0194BBA63616" box="[862,1002,1530,1555]" captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="5.[160,235,1259,1282]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetId="figure-112@5.[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 2–7. Holotype of Solaropsis caperata MZSP 144000 (W = 50.2 mm): 2, apical view; 3, inferior view; 4, left view; 5, apertural view; 6, detail of region half a whorl preceding the peristome, showing characteristic depression, dorsal-slightly inferior view; 7, detail of apical region, apical view, scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457015/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Figures 2, 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAD6328FC6D0194BC3A3616" box="[1020,1142,1530,1555]" captionStart="Figures 10–16" captionStartId="7.[160,235,840,863]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetId="figure-3@7.[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 10–16. Paratypes of Solaropsis caperata. 10, MZSP 154136 (W 45.1 mm), frontal view; 11, same apical view; 12, same, inferior view; 13, MZSP 154137 (W 39.0 mm), frontal view; 14, same, frontalslightly inferior view to show depression; 15, same, apical view; 16, inferior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457021/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">11 and 15</figureCitation>
). Teleoconch ~3 whorls; sculpture consisting of growth lines producing narrow undulations, mainly close to superior suture, and rounded granules over whorls (Figures –10). Colour beige, with stains mainly in superior surface, orange colour in first two whorls, gradually darkening to brown until last whorl forming mosaic of coalescent spots usually in opisthocline bands. Inferior surface almost uniformly beige, with scanty dark, narrow, axial spots in periphery (
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAC6329FDFC01DABA9535C8" box="[621,729,1460,1485]" captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="5.[160,235,1259,1282]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetId="figure-112@5.[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 2–7. Holotype of Solaropsis caperata MZSP 144000 (W = 50.2 mm): 2, apical view; 3, inferior view; 4, left view; 5, apertural view; 6, detail of region half a whorl preceding the peristome, showing characteristic depression, dorsal-slightly inferior view; 7, detail of apical region, apical view, scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457015/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Figures 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAC6329FD7B01DABB2835C8" box="[746,868,1460,1485]" captionStart="Figures 10–16" captionStartId="7.[160,235,840,863]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetId="figure-3@7.[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 10–16. Paratypes of Solaropsis caperata. 10, MZSP 154136 (W 45.1 mm), frontal view; 11, same apical view; 12, same, inferior view; 13, MZSP 154137 (W 39.0 mm), frontal view; 14, same, frontalslightly inferior view to show depression; 15, same, apical view; 16, inferior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457021/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">12 and 16</figureCitation>
). Two deep depressions located half a whorl from peristome (
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAC6329FDF901B8BAB935EA" box="[616,757,1494,1519]" captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="5.[160,235,1259,1282]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetId="figure-112@5.[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 2–7. Holotype of Solaropsis caperata MZSP 144000 (W = 50.2 mm): 2, apical view; 3, inferior view; 4, left view; 5, apertural view; 6, detail of region half a whorl preceding the peristome, showing characteristic depression, dorsal-slightly inferior view; 7, detail of apical region, apical view, scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457015/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Figures 3, 6</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAC6329FCAB01B8BB3235EA" box="[826,894,1494,1519]" captionStart="Figures 10–16" captionStartId="7.[160,235,840,863]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetId="figure-3@7.[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 10–16. Paratypes of Solaropsis caperata. 10, MZSP 154136 (W 45.1 mm), frontal view; 11, same apical view; 12, same, inferior view; 13, MZSP 154137 (W 39.0 mm), frontal view; 14, same, frontalslightly inferior view to show depression; 15, same, apical view; 16, inferior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457021/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">12–14</figureCitation>
), larger one elliptical, projected to periphery, ~1/6 whorl in length; smaller depression parallel to larger one, turned inferiorly, spirally elongated (
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAC6329FDEE0272BB493630" box="[639,773,1564,1589]" captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="5.[160,235,1259,1282]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetId="figure-112@5.[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 2–7. Holotype of Solaropsis caperata MZSP 144000 (W = 50.2 mm): 2, apical view; 3, inferior view; 4, left view; 5, apertural view; 6, detail of region half a whorl preceding the peristome, showing characteristic depression, dorsal-slightly inferior view; 7, detail of apical region, apical view, scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457015/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Figures 3, 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAC6329FC850272BBC43630" box="[788,904,1564,1589]" captionStart="Figures 10–16" captionStartId="7.[160,235,840,863]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetId="figure-3@7.[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 10–16. Paratypes of Solaropsis caperata. 10, MZSP 154136 (W 45.1 mm), frontal view; 11, same apical view; 12, same, inferior view; 13, MZSP 154137 (W 39.0 mm), frontal view; 14, same, frontalslightly inferior view to show depression; 15, same, apical view; 16, inferior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457021/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">12 and 14</figureCitation>
). Last half whorl with weak peripheral carina, located along its middle region (
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAC6329FCA70250BBED3652" box="[822,929,1598,1623]" captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="5.[160,235,1259,1282]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetId="figure-112@5.[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 2–7. Holotype of Solaropsis caperata MZSP 144000 (W = 50.2 mm): 2, apical view; 3, inferior view; 4, left view; 5, apertural view; 6, detail of region half a whorl preceding the peristome, showing characteristic depression, dorsal-slightly inferior view; 7, detail of apical region, apical view, scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457015/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Figures 4</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAC6329FC4E0250BBB73652" box="[991,1019,1598,1623]" captionStart="Figures 10–16" captionStartId="7.[160,235,840,863]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetId="figure-3@7.[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 10–16. Paratypes of Solaropsis caperata. 10, MZSP 154136 (W 45.1 mm), frontal view; 11, same apical view; 12, same, inferior view; 13, MZSP 154137 (W 39.0 mm), frontal view; 14, same, frontalslightly inferior view to show depression; 15, same, apical view; 16, inferior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457021/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">13</figureCitation>
). Peristome wide, ~70% of shell height, ~52% of shell width (
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAC6329FD59020FBB7C367F" box="[712,816,1633,1658]" captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="5.[160,235,1259,1282]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetId="figure-112@5.[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 2–7. Holotype of Solaropsis caperata MZSP 144000 (W = 50.2 mm): 2, apical view; 3, inferior view; 4, left view; 5, apertural view; 6, detail of region half a whorl preceding the peristome, showing characteristic depression, dorsal-slightly inferior view; 7, detail of apical region, apical view, scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457015/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Figures 5</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAC6329FCF9020FBBC8367F" box="[872,900,1633,1658]" captionStart="Figures 10–16" captionStartId="7.[160,235,840,863]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetId="figure-3@7.[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 10–16. Paratypes of Solaropsis caperata. 10, MZSP 154136 (W 45.1 mm), frontal view; 11, same apical view; 12, same, inferior view; 13, MZSP 154137 (W 39.0 mm), frontal view; 14, same, frontalslightly inferior view to show depression; 15, same, apical view; 16, inferior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457021/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">10</figureCitation>
); superior 2/3 strongly convex, callus narrow and thin; inferior 1/3 notched, performing angle ~40°, incompletely covering umbilicus; outer lip performing wide arc, with ample notch (~120°) correspondent to carina. Umbilicus open, occupying ~10% of inferior area (
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAF632AFF3904BAB96330E8" box="[168,303,212,237]" captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="5.[160,235,1259,1282]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetId="figure-112@5.[163,1153,142,1228]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 2–7. Holotype of Solaropsis caperata MZSP 144000 (W = 50.2 mm): 2, apical view; 3, inferior view; 4, left view; 5, apertural view; 6, detail of region half a whorl preceding the peristome, showing characteristic depression, dorsal-slightly inferior view; 7, detail of apical region, apical view, scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457015/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Figures 3, 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="26EE2A76FFAF632AFEAA04BAB9FE30E8" box="[315,434,212,237]" captionStart="Figures 10–16" captionStartId="7.[160,235,840,863]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetId="figure-3@7.[163,1153,142,808]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 10–16. Paratypes of Solaropsis caperata. 10, MZSP 154136 (W 45.1 mm), frontal view; 11, same apical view; 12, same, inferior view; 13, MZSP 154137 (W 39.0 mm), frontal view; 14, same, frontalslightly inferior view to show depression; 15, same, apical view; 16, inferior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457021/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">12 and 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="EAAA667BFFAC6329FF310085B962355F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457015" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6457015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457015/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" startId="5.[160,235,1259,1282]" targetBox="[163,1153,142,1228]" targetPageId="5">
